result.name: Red Tea Cafe

reviews.text: There are several RTC in town. This one is the best. High CP value. Satay beef is my favourite.

Local restaurant but clean and modern. There are 4-5 daily lunch around ¥40-60. Everyday has long queue and takes 15-30min for entering restaurant, so early lunch just 12:00 or later like 14:00 are better for time saving.

Red tea lives up to its hype. Love the energy from the guy who manages the queue. There’s always a long queue during lunch but it moves very quickly due to the staff rushing customers out. Good portions for the price (lunch is $50-60) - especially if you don’t eat rice/carbs. Cutlery is a bit dirty so remember to bring some tissue to clean them.

The menu is quite elaborate, there should be something for everyone. Reasonably priced, tasty and, orders are prepared and served quickly. The place is very busy throughout the day, but there is plenty of seating. So, waiting for a seat is usually short. It may not be a suitable place for quiet meal because it can be very noisy in there.

Had breakfast here, breakfast is served between 7.00 am and 11.30 am. Typical  Chinese style western cafe. Very busy with many customers. Decor is quite typical of such a restaurant. Prices are moderate. Ordered  fried fish, scrambled  eggs, sausage and toast. Arrived hot and portion was very big. Taste is OK.

One thing that I do not like is their use of plastic teaspoons served with their tea and coffee, they should use reusable cutlery and avoid plastic.

lt should be noted that there are some servers who are particularly rude and obnoxious.
